<?xml-stylesheet type="text/xsl" href="../assets/xml/rss.xsl" media="all"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Lacking Natural Simplicity (Posts about macsOS)</title><link>https://tkurtbond.github.io/</link><description></description><atom:link href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/categories/macsos.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"></atom:link><language>en</language><copyright>Contents Â© 2023 &lt;a href="mailto:tkurtbond@gmail.com"&gt;T. Kurt Bond&lt;/a&gt; </copyright><lastBuildDate>Sun, 19 Feb 2023 19:01:01 GMT</lastBuildDate><generator>Nikola (getnikola.com)</generator><docs>http://blogs.law.harvard.edu/tech/rss</docs><item><title>Compiling s7 scheme on macOS</title><link>https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2020/08/03/compiling-s7-scheme-on-macos/</link><dc:creator>T. Kurt Bond</dc:creator><description>&lt;p&gt;To compile &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://ccrma.stanford.edu/software/snd/snd/s7.html"&gt;s7 scheme&lt;/a&gt; with a standalone &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/pages/computer-vocabulary/#REPL"&gt;REPL&lt;/a&gt;, s7's home page says to
add the empty file &lt;span class="file"&gt;mus-config.h&lt;/span&gt; to the source directory, then
(in Linux):&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_f186f3897b3c42cd8c65dab7c053ff4c-1" name="rest_code_f186f3897b3c42cd8c65dab7c053ff4c-1" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2020/08/03/compiling-s7-scheme-on-macos/#rest_code_f186f3897b3c42cd8c65dab7c053ff4c-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;gcc&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;s7.c&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-o&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;repl&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-DWITH_MAIN&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-I.&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-O2&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-g&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-ldl&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-lm&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-Wl,-export-dynamic
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It turns out that on macOS, whose &lt;span class="command"&gt;ld&lt;/span&gt; (from clang) doesn't
understand &lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;&lt;span class="pre"&gt;-export-dynamic&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;, you have to do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_f568a6bc37154ca59359506cb8a9f433-1" name="rest_code_f568a6bc37154ca59359506cb8a9f433-1" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2020/08/03/compiling-s7-scheme-on-macos/#rest_code_f568a6bc37154ca59359506cb8a9f433-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;gcc&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;s7.c&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-o&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;repl&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-DWITH_MAIN&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-I.&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-O2&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-g&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-ldl&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-lm&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;-Wl,-dynamic
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Then you need to do&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_488827bfce3444e0870abff671b02407-1" name="rest_code_488827bfce3444e0870abff671b02407-1" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2020/08/03/compiling-s7-scheme-on-macos/#rest_code_488827bfce3444e0870abff671b02407-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;./repl&lt;span class="w"&gt; &lt;/span&gt;libc.scm
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which seems to generate &lt;span class="file"&gt;libc_s7.c&lt;/span&gt; and compile it into
&lt;span class="file"&gt;libc_s.so&lt;/span&gt;.   Then you can run the &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/pages/computer-vocabulary/#REPL"&gt;REPL&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class="code"&gt;&lt;pre class="code bash"&gt;&lt;a id="rest_code_fc43eb84b6874cff86c5d1797c13e463-1" name="rest_code_fc43eb84b6874cff86c5d1797c13e463-1" href="https://tkurtbond.github.io/posts/2020/08/03/compiling-s7-scheme-on-macos/#rest_code_fc43eb84b6874cff86c5d1797c13e463-1"&gt;&lt;/a&gt;./repl
&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;which, from looking at &lt;span class="file"&gt;s7.c&lt;/span&gt;, loads &lt;span class="file"&gt;repl.scm&lt;/span&gt;.
Unfortunately, I don't understand the repl commands, except for
&lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;pwd&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;cd&lt;/code&gt;.  Oh, and &lt;code class="docutils literal"&gt;(exit)&lt;/code&gt; exits the repl.&lt;/p&gt;
